// Man page for xclip
manXclip="XCLIP(1)                         X Shell Manual                         XCLIP(1)

<b>NAME</b>
    xc - Clipboard utility for text storage

<b>SYNOPSIS</b>
    <b>xc</b>
    <b>xc</b> TEXT
    <b>xc --number</b> [NUMBER]
    <b>xc</b> [-p] [INDEX]
    <b>xc --clear</b>

<b>DESCRIPTION</b>
    Basic clipboard utility for storing and retrieving text values. The
    clipboard resets when the terminal session closes. Useful for holding
    temporary data in scripts or between commands. Supports redirects with
    > and >> operators. The --post flag allows appending from standard input.
    Redirect input is never printed to the terminal for security.

<b>OPTIONS</b>
    <b>xc</b> - View Clipboard
      Display all current clipboard contents.
      Shows all stored entries with their indices.

    <b>xc TEXT</b> - Append Text
      Append text string to clipboard.
      Creates new entry at next available index.

    <b>xc --number</b> [NUMBER] - Append Number
      Append numeric value to clipboard.
      Stores number as separate entry.

    <b>xc</b> [-p] [INDEX] - Retrieve Entry
      Return clipboard value at specified index.
      Use -p flag for passive retrieval without display.

    <b>xc --clear</b> - Clear Clipboard
      Remove all entries from clipboard.
      Resets clipboard to empty state.

<b>EXAMPLE:</b>
    <color=#e4ff34># Basic Usage</color>
    <b>xc</b>
        View all clipboard entries

    <b>xc password123</b>
        Store password in clipboard

    <color=#e4ff34># Store Values</color>
    <b>xc --number 192</b>
        Store numeric value

    <b>xc target.local</b>
        Store hostname

    <color=#e4ff34># Retrieve Values</color>
    <b>xc 0</b>
        Get first clipboard entry

    <b>xc -p 1</b>
        Passive retrieval of second entry

    <color=#e4ff34># Script Usage</color>
    <b>xc exploit_data</b>
        Store data for later use

    <b>pass=xc(0)</b>
        Retrieve in script variable

    <color=#e4ff34># Clear Clipboard</color>
    <b>xc --clear</b>
        Remove all entries

    <color=#e4ff34># Redirect Input</color>
    <b>cat passwords.txt > xc</b>
        Redirect file to clipboard

    <b>scan -l >> xc</b>
        Append scan output

<b>SEE ALSO</b>
    <b>cat</b>, <b>echo</b>, <b>editor</b>, <b>write</b>, <b>vi</b>"